    public override async Task SeedAsync()
    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Navigating the App",
            Slug = "navigating-the-app-overview",
            Summary = "An overview of the side menu, header bar, notifications, search, theme switching, and how to get around the app.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            IsOnboardingRequired = true,
            SortOrder = 2,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["onboarding","navigation"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Navigating the App\n\nEvery page in Forge shares the same layout: a side menu on the left, a header bar across the top, and your content in the middle.\n\n### The Side Menu\n\nThe side menu is how you move around the app. When it's narrow, you see just icons. Click the arrow at the top to widen it and show the full labels. Forge remembers your choice on this browser.\n\nThe menu is organized into groups, not one long list. **Dashboard** stays pinned at the very top. Click any group to open its items. The menu also opens the group for the page you're on. You only see the groups and items your role and your company's setup include, so anything not turned on simply won't appear.\n\n**Menu groups (in order):**\n- **Dashboard** (pinned at top) — your daily home page with widgets\n- **Operations** — Board, Backlog, Planning, Calendar, Approvals\n- **Sales** — Customers, Leads, Quotes, Sales Orders, Recurring Orders, Shipments, Customer Returns, Invoices, Payments\n- **Production** — Parts, MRP, Scheduling, Lots, OEE\n- **Inventory** — Stock, Assets, Maintenance\n- **Purchasing** — Vendors, Purchase Orders, RFQs, Payables\n- **People** — Employees, Time, Expenses, Training\n- **Insights** — Reports, AI\n- **Accounting** — Trial Balance, Profit & Loss, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow, AR Aging, AP Aging, GRNI, Period Close, Bank Reconciliation (the full accounting suite is optional and only shows if your company turns it on)\n\nPinned at the **bottom** are **Shop Floor** (the kiosk display) and **Admin** (system setup, which opens into Users & Access, Master Data, Integrations, Workflow, Capabilities, and System).\n\nA few things live outside the side menu, even though people often look there:\n- **Chat** opens from the chat icon in the top bar, not the side menu.\n- **Account** (your profile, compliance, and security) lives in your picture menu at the top-right.\n- **Calendar**, **AI**, and **Training** sit inside groups (Operations, Insights, and People) rather than as their own top-level links.\n\n### The Header Bar\n\nThe header bar stays put at the top of every page. It has:\n- **Search** — search across jobs, parts, customers, vendors, and more\n- **Notification bell** — shows how many unread notifications you have; click to open them\n- **Chat** — opens the chat panel and shows unread messages\n- **Theme switch** — a sun/moon icon that flips between light and dark\n- **Your picture** — opens your menu with account settings, language, and log out\n\n### Switching the Theme\n\nClick the sun/moon icon in the header to switch between light and dark. Your choice is saved and applies right away across your open tabs.\n\n### Keyboard Shortcuts\n\nPress **/** (the forward slash key) anywhere to see the keyboard shortcuts. Handy ones:\n- **Ctrl+K** — jump to search\n- **/** — open the shortcuts list\n- **Escape** — close the open panel or window\n\n### Bookmarking and Sharing Views\n\nYour current view is captured in the web address, so:\n- You can bookmark any page, tab, or filtered view\n- The browser back and forward buttons work as expected\n- Sharing the address opens the same view for the other person\n- Refreshing the page keeps you where you were","sections":[]}"""
        });

